## Server/headless strain: no desktop environment package at all.
## openssh-server lives here (and in cloud.list.chroot), NOT base.list.chroot:
## a headless server wants sshd on first boot, but the desktop strains
## (laptop/workstation/handheld/lowspec) never asked for an open :22, so it
## must not ship universally. Runtime hardening (key-only auth, no root login)
## is still applied by modes/server/setup/01-install-ssh.sh on
## `distro-modectl switch server`; baking the package in just means sshd exists
## before that runs. Docker/Netdata stay out, left to modes/server/setup/*.sh --
## same lean-image philosophy as iso/README.md's main scope decision.
openssh-server
